    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, the Zurich Zebras lean heavily on **Yordan Alvarez** (71.69) and **Trea Turner** (70.89) as our primary anchors. **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a strong xwOBA of 0.393 against a vulnerable Castillo, while **Trea Turner** remains our premier weapon for stolen base accumulation; facing Pfaadt, who allows a slow delivery, **Trea Turner** gains a 4% efficiency boost specifically for his sprint-heavy profile. We are also bullish on **Kyle Schwarber** (65.10), whose elite 0.402 xwOBA and favorable #2 spot in the order make him an excellent pairing with **Trea Turner** to maximize run production against a middling pitcher.\n\nWe have strategically avoided several high-floor options to maintain our Roto efficiency. **Colt Keith** (64.95) and **Logan O'Hoppe** (64.67) represent our strongest mid-tier starters, both benefiting from highly favorable SP_xERA matchups above 4.00. The most difficult personnel decision was benching **Carson Benge** (36.95), whose projection plummeted due to a difficult L/L platoon disadvantage against Lopez; despite his potential, he fell well below our 40.0 floor threshold. Similarly, **Victor Scott II** (36.28) was omitted to preserve our game caps, as his elite speed is mitigated today by a poor matchup against Suarez and an unfavorable #9 batting position that restricts his RBI opportunities.\n\nWhile we are optimistic, owners should remain cautious of the matchup for **Christian Yelich** (39.38). He faces a stiff test against Griffin, who boasts a sub-2.00 xERA, leading to a significant downward adjustment on his base projection. Furthermore, **Junior Caminero** (51.99) is starting despite a suppressed score caused by a difficult park factor and a tough draw against Fried; he remains a marginal play that we are monitoring closely. We are keeping **Kazuma Okamoto** and **Zac Veen** locked on the bench as they are currently unavailable for selection, and we will monitor for any late lineup shifts affecting **Dillon Dingler** or **Hyeseong Kim** to ensure our efficiency targets remain intact.",
